name: PureGym

name: Northern lights
summary: Multiple news outlets are reporting sightings of the Northern Lights across the UK, including in England, Wales, and Scotland. This is due to a severe solar storm that has caused increased activity on the sun's surface, leading to the release of charged particles that interact with Earth's magnetic field to create the aurora borealis. The Northern Lights are typically visible in higher latitudes, but the current solar storm has made them visible even in southern parts of the UK. The best time to view the Northern Lights is during clear, dark nights, and using a camera phone to capture the display is recommended.

name: Magna Carta
summary: Environmental activists from the Just Stop Oil group targeted the British Library's copy of the Magna Carta, an iconic historical document. Two elderly protesters, aged 82 and 85, used a hammer and chisel to damage the protective glass case of the artifact. The protesters' aim was to draw attention to the urgency of addressing climate change. The incident has sparked outrage, as the Magna Carta is considered a precious symbol of constitutional rights and democratic values.
